[1] Russia (Astrachan)
Date: Sat 21 Jul 2012
Source: Provintsiya.ru [in Russia, trans. Mod.CP, edited]
http://www.province.ru/astrakhan/news/events/in_astrakhan_recorded_outbreak_of_measles/


During the past 3 years, the Astrakhan oblast was considered to have been a region free from measles. But now the situation has changed. According to the head physician of the Regional Infectious Diseases Hospital, most new measles cases have occurred in the Leninsky district of Astrakhan oblast. Initially, these cases were believed to have been imported from other regions. But now there are indigenous cases of measles. This is due to the fact that many children have not been vaccinated against the disease in infancy. This situation is a consequence of deficiencies in the regional outpatient service. For instance, the most recent measles case, a child aged one year 2 months, was unvaccinated.

