Africa
------
[3] Nigeria
Date: Thu 19 Jul 2012
Source: Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), Federal Ministry of Health - Nigeria, Weekly Epidemiology Report Issue: Volume 2 No. 27 13 Jul 2012 [edited]


Update on suspected cases of Measles in Nigeria as of 13 Jul 2012
-----------------------------------------------------------------
5.1. In the reporting week 27 (2012), 64 suspected cases of measles with 0 deaths were reported from 14 states. Between weeks 1-27 2012, a total of 7371 suspected measles cases, 466 laboratory confirmed and 102 deaths (CFR 1.38 percent) were recorded.

5.2. NPHCDA and partners have launched an outbreak response strategy in 72 LGAs across the country.

