[6] Australia (Travel alert response)
Date: Mon 16 Jul 2012
From: Suzanne McEvoy <Suzanne.McEvoy@health.wa.gov.au> [edited]


[The following comment has been received from Suzanne McEvoy regarding the moderator's statement in part [1] of Measles update 2012 (28) 20120715.1202611 with regard to travel alerts that: "It must be presumed that these alerts have achieved their propose, and the travelling public has responded positively." Sadly, this comment is incorrect. ProMED-mail appreciates Suzanne McEvoy's help in keeping the record straight. - Mod.CP]

"I am aware of several cases of measles in Australia that have been related to attendance at recent international sporting events. Firstly, a resident of the Northern Territory acquired infection while attending the Football World Cup held in South Africa in 2010.

Secondly, there were 3 cases of confirmed measles in Western Australians who independently acquired infection while attending the Rugby Union World Cup held in New Zealand in late 2011. All of these cases were young or middle-aged adult men. It seems likely that there are other such measles infections internationally that are not reported through the media or in the peer-reviewed literature, and hence may not come to the attention of ProMED."

--
Suzanne McEvoy
<Suzanne.McEvoy@health.wa.gov.au>

